RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIKE OPERATOR sped to the front in the two path, dueled inside DR. TROUTMAN up the backstretch, inched ahead on the far turn, shook free at the top of the stretch and remained clear under urging. DIVINE FEMININE traveled along the inside into the first turn then moved into the two path, saved ground at the back around the far turn, moved to within range of the winner entering the final furlong but finished evenly late. MONGOLIAN KINGDOM settled in the two path, traveled outside a rival to the far turn, angled out and came four wide into the stretch and was along for the show. WARRENS CANDY MAN pressed from inside early then chased the top pair up the backstretch, rounded the far turn two then three wide and weakened. DR. TROUTMAN chased three wide early, went up to duel three deep then outside MIKE OPERATOR on the backstretch, stayed alongside through the far turn while moving further off the rail, lost touch with the winner four wide into the drive and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PINECONE pressed three deep then dueled from outside, inched ahead at the five-sixteenths pole, put away inner rival in upper stretch and was kept to task to the wire. MISS MIND CHANGER got pinballed leaving the gate, trailed up the backstretch, chased two then three wide on the turn, got floated out leaving the bend and rallied to the best the rest. WE'LL DO IT LIVE bumped at the start, dueled for the lead inside SPIRIT RULES early then chased the outer leaders leaving the backstretch, drifted out into the lane, drifted back inside in the stretch and churned on for the show. SPIRIT RULES bobbled and bumped inner rival at the start, dueled between early then inside PINE CONE into and around the turn while in the two path, fought with that rival to upper stretch and weakened. SOPHIE JEAN stalked the leaders up the backstretch, saved ground from the rail through the turn and lacked the needed response.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, dueled inside, chased, drifted out turn, in str

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG SWEDE broke a step slow, climbed at the rear early, chased four wide around the bend, rallied four deep midstretch and edged away from CURLY ESA late. CURLY ESA hopped at the start, chased four then three wide around the bend, bid three deep midstretch, dueled with BIG SWEDE in the final sixteenth and got outkicked. SONIC BREES pressed the pace from outside, chased the leader three then two wide around the bend, challenged again between rivals entering the final furlong, flattened in deep stretch but saved the show. FAST PER SE set the pace under pressure up the backstretch, cleared around the bend and angled to the inside, drifted out midstretch and yielded in the late stages and missed the show. ECONOMICAL stalked up close from inside, saved ground through the turn, moved out a bit in upper stretch and weakened. PAPALE chased four deep between rivals and got crowded a bit at the nine-sixteenths pole, chased three wide exiting the backstretch then moved into the two path, steered out in the lane and lacked a rally.

ENTRY.OWNER: Riggio Dolores and Valdez Jose R
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, climbed, 4wide, rallied 4deep best late

ENTRY.NAME: Sonic Brees
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, chased 3-2wide, bid between, flattened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUST BE YOU stalked between foes then in the two path on the clubhouse turn, took aim three wide into the stretch, split foes in upper stretch to take control and powered away to win convincingly. SHE'S MY NIECE broke out, stalked three deep into the clubhouse turn then got floated out to the four path by ARCTIC BREEZE drifting out around the bend, bid three deep on the far turn, was no match for the winner in the stretch and churned on for a clear second. ARCTIC BREEZE sped to the front in the two path, jumped the shadow from the light tower on the clubhouse turn and drifted briefly to three path, dueled outside OUTSPOKEN up the backstretch and around the far turn, vied with rivals on both sides leaving that bend and weakened in the furlong grounds. CALIFORNIA CODE got floated out leaving the gate, chased four wide at the back early, three then four wide on the far turn, tipped out into the lane and weakened. OUTSPOKEN chased briefly from inside then went up to take control around the clubhouse turn, dueled inside ARCTIC BREEZE in the middle stages and far turn, fought to upper stretch and tired.

ENTRY.OWNER: Eclipse Thoroughbred Partners and Repole Stable

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ULTRA POWER bumped leaving the gate, chased briefly then went up to duel from inside, shook free from TAPALO midstretch and drew away. NESSO'S LASTHARRAH broke inward, went up to duel for command then ceded command, stalked the top pair three wide into the turn, came out and entered the lane six wide, finished willingly down the lane and bested the others. MIRACLE MARK broke in and bumped rival, was prominent early between rivals then got put in tight and steadied at the five-eighths pole, went four wide into the turn, moved out to the five path briefly then angled inward and exited the bend three wide, summoned a mild rally but could not get by NESSO'S LASTHARRAH for second. TAPALO dueled for command from outside, fought five wide into the stretch and weakened down the lane. POTENTIAL SPAM got brushed at the start, saved ground through the turn off the pace, moved off the fence in the drive and failed to menace. SIR LOOKING GLASS had to take up between foes early, trailed three wide into the turn, spun four wide into the lane, eased through the stretch and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BETTY'S SONG sprinted clear quickly, led two then three wide through the turn, remained under confident handling to the three-sixteenths pole, then was coaxed along lightly and drew off easily. WARREN'S SHOW BIZZ sat off the pace, ridden along two then three wide on the turn, steered out in the stretch run, put in a mild rally and gained the place. HOLLYWOOD RUMOR chased off the rail, two wide around the turn, was no match for the winner in the lane and got outkicked for second. MISS COMMANDER chased three deep into the turn, three to four wide around the bend, drifted out in the lane and weakened. OCEAN OF LIES chased along the rail, saved ground to the stretch and faded out of contention. HAMMETT trailed five wide around the bend and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 52000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SONG OF SHADOWS dueled for the lead from outside, cleared at the five-sixteenths pole, drifted out while meeting the bid from SHANGHAI SUNRISE in the lane, turned that foe away past the eighth pole and was ridden out to the wire. SHANGHAI SUNRISE prominent early between rivals then stalked the top pair up the backstretch, angled out on the turn and came four wide into the stretch, moved out further while launching a bid outside SONG OF SHADOWS, was turned away in the furlong grounds and stayed on to secure second. FLYMETOTHEMOONBABY chased along the inside into and around the bend, steered out into the drive and summoned a mild rally to earn the show honors. DIAMONDS DANZING stumbled badly and bumped leaving the gate ran up on the heels of the leader and had to check approaching the half-mile pole, traveled along the inside then two wide into the lane and finished evenly past the eighth pole. KISS MY KAT dueled inside SONG OF SHADOWS, fought around the turn then failed to kick on with the winner past the five-sixteenths pole and weakened down the lane. DANCING SOUL stumbled and broke in to bump DIAMONDS DANZING at the start, chased wide up the backstretch, bid three deep into the turn, could not sustain the challenged late on the bend and faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT SPECIAL vied four deep then three deep into the turn, dueled three wide into the lane, shook free in upper stretch and padded the margin in the final furlong. AROUND THE DIAL bothered shortly after the start then started to climb at the back, lacked room behind rivals from the five-sixteenths pole to the quarter pole, rallied between rivals at the three-sixteenths marker, split foes again past the eight pole and gained the place. BIG CHEDDAR vied five deep up the backstretch, four deep into the turn, dueled in the four path entering the lane, could not kick on with the winner in upper stretch, flattened out but was able to secure the show honors. AWESOME HEIGHTS chased off the inside, went three to four wide into the lane and lacked a rally. BOUND TO BET vied for command from inside, failed to kick on with outer rivals past the five-sixteenths pole and flattened out in the lane. MIDNIGHT LIGHTNING chased four wide into the turn, exited the bend six wide and lacked a rally. ABADON vied between foes for command, got put in tight and checked into the turn, chased two wide into the lane and weakened. MAJESTIC WIND vied three deep between foes up the backstretch, two wide into the turn, chased two wide past the three-eighths pole, angled five wide into the lane and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1M Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 52000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winner s Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COWBOY MIKE dueled three wide around the first turn, cleared leaving the backstretch, led three wide into the stretch, asked right handed past the eighth pole and was ridden out to the wire. BUCK OWENS chased four deep on the clubhouse turn, went two wide into the far turn, angled out and came five wide into the stretch, kept on through the lane and bested the others. WINE AND WHISKY stalked between rivals, got bumped and put in tight, having to check past the three-quarter pole, chased three wide into the lane, churned on down the stretch and got edged for second. JERRY JEFF WALKER raced up close four wide, came in to bother rivals past the three-quarter pole, rounded the far turn three then four wide and weakened. GALOPING CAT dueled for command from inside, chased the winner leaving the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and faded. LUKA GRAZIE stalked along the rail, drifted out and bumped rival past the three-quarter pole, chased between then two wide on the far turn and weakened. STAR PROSPECT tracked three deep around the first turn, got bumped, crowded and checked past the three-quarter pole, remained off the rail and spun four wide into the lane and came up empty. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE INCIDENT BETWEEN SEVERAL RIVALS EARLY ON THE BACKSTRETCH. FOLLOWING A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT ALTHOUGH LUKA GRAZIE AND JERRY JEFF WALKER BOTHERED WINE AND WHISKY AND STAR PROSPECT PAST THE THREE-QUARTER POLE, THE INCIDENT DID NOT WARRANT A DISQUALIFICATION.
